RNN-T greedy decoder hotword (contextual) biasing.

Vendored patch against kdrkdrkdr/nemotron-asr-streaming.c @ 4fde8b47
(NEMOTRON_C_REF in the Dockerfile). Applied in the builder stage with `git
apply` right after the shared-lib and set-att-right patches.

Adds `nemo_set_hotwords(ctx, ids, lens, n, boost)` to the public API.
Hotword phrases (token-id sequences) are stored in nemo_ctx_t (global, set
once at boot). During greedy decode, `boost` is added to the logit of any
token that starts or continues a phrase, nudging the argmax toward known
vocabulary. boost == 0 or n == 0 clears biasing. No-op when inactive.

Active partial matches are tracked per-stream in nemo_rnnt_stream_t and
persist across encoder frames (blank frames do not advance them).

